Infitweaker is used to modify environment settings of Freetype library with Infinality Patches

This GUI provides a quick way to test different infinality-settings.sh values

For Infinality patches, visit http://www.infinality.net/forum/


Infitweaker requires:
Python
PyGTK
Python Imaging Library (PIL)
NumPy

Install on Fedora:
su -c 'yum install python numpy pygtk2 python-imaging'

Install freetype-py:
wget http://freetype-py.googlecode.com/files/freetype-py-0.3.3.tar.gz
tar xfvz freetype-py-0.3.3.tar.gz
cd freetype-py-0.3.3
su -c './setup.py install'


To start Infitweaker, from shell run: ./start.sh

Python code was developed using Ecplise with PyDev
infitweaker.glade was developed with Glade Interface Designer, Glade 2 in Fedora 16

